  "tcmTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "Deer antler is a salty, warming substance that enters the liver and kidney meridians. It is used for reinforcing kidney yang, replenishing vital essence and blood, tonifying, strengthening sinews and bones, and invigorating in general. It can be used to treat symptoms of kidney yang deficiency such as impotence, soreness and weakness of the lower back and knees, dizziness and tinnitus. It is also used to strengthen bones, sinews and joints that have been weakened due to liver and kidney deficiencies.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "鹿茸為著名的補陽中藥，藥味甘、鹹，藥性溫，歸於腎、肝經，能壯腎陽、益精血、強筋骨、調沖任、托瘡毒，用於腎陽不足引起的性功能下降、月經不調、尿頻、頭暈、耳聲嘈雜、腰膝酸痛、四肢不溫等，可單服或配合人蔘、巴戟天等中藥使用。\n",
    "zh-Hans": "鹿茸为著名的补阳中药，药味甘、咸，药性溫，歸于肾、肝经，能壮肾阳、益精血、强筋骨、调沖任、托瘡毒，用于肾阳不足引起的性功能下降、月经不调、尿頻、头暈、耳聲嘈雜、腰膝酸痛、四肢不溫等，可單服或配合人参、巴戟天等中药使用。\n"
  },
